			  edge1
title "On the Edge of the Abyss"
descr "   An awesome sight assails your eyes.  Before you lies the Abyss.  Your
senses swim as you look straight down into the infinite.  A blackness that
chills your soul matches the wind that freezes your marrow.  Screams and
wails of souls falling into the deepest depths of hell tear at your ears.
The ledge under your feet is barely wide enough to pass but craggy enough
to climb.  To the north and south the ledge skirts the edge of the Abyss.
>From the west a gale force wind chills your bones and blocks your retreat.
There are several scratches and claw marks along the edge."

extra {"scratches", "marks", "claw marks", "edge"}
"The marks seem to have been left by souls attempting escape from the Abyss.
They read 'Salvation lies in our markings, we escaped as the clock turns'."

